cher and scholar of Byzantium in particular, and for every bibliophile in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aByzanz. 4aHandschrift. 4aPaläographie. 7aHISTORY / Byzantine Empire.2bisacsh  aByzantium.  amanuscripts.  apalaeography.  atexts.1 aAgoritsas, Demetrios C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAngold, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntonopoulos, Panagiotis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBianconi, Daniele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChrysos, Evangelos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDendrinos, Charalambos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDendrinos, Charalambos, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEasterling, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiarenis, Ilias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiarenis, Ilias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGioffreda, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIoannides, Archim. Gregorios A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKafasis, Christos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagdalino, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartín, Inmaculada Pérez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNesseris, Ilias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNousia, Fevronia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalau, Annaclara Cataldi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators